title: Why I am betting on artificial heart IIT-K is developing
Show HN: Conv911, a social-media platform to improve at texting
text:
This is a web app we built for fun, basically a social-media platform for people to get help with their online interactions, like answering your boss, a colleague, or just handling any random conversation.

I know some people were concerned with ethical issues with such website, which is why we made a clear guideline on the type of content which should be posted there. As an introvert it often occurred to me to spend a week before answering an email, or spend hours to answer a random discord conv, this is the kind of helpful use-cases we are aiming for.

I know HN is usually interested in more technical topics, but any raw feedback is appreciated :) The website is built with React/Tailwind on the frontend and Rust for the backend

From Both Sides Now
Dear Twitter, thank you for suspending my account, otherwise I'd gladly pay $99
text:
Twitter is truly a magical place in sense that it can wake up the worst monster inside even the nicest person. Example is my elder mother, the sweetest person you met, but trolls and clowns on Twitter that she constantly engage with turn her into someone I never knew I would experience. Its very sad.

Now personally I am the calmest person you witness, but it takes less than 5 minutes of twitter scrolling to get me engaged with some idiot being wrong. Sometimes its a conversation that I follow and that conversation triggers me and I need to join wasting time and being angry. But not anymore! Just few months ago, in response to someone calling me bold (actually random avatar, far from bold/ing), I called them fat - apparently something that is on Twitter ban list, and my account got switched into "read only" mode. I could refresh and read newest content, but not follow or reply/tweet. Obviously I immediately went into wanting to appeal that decision... but then I realized - "let me try to use Twitter like this." And oh boy let me tell you how wonderful my experience is! Sometimes I still get to read idiots and nasty people's comments... but my own awareness that I cannot simply join them and waste my time and get myself angry, that blessing is simply worth $99 that I would otherwise gladly pay Twitter each and every month to have this blessing of a "read only" Twitter account.

End of the story.
